Interface Decider

  • All Known Subinterfaces:

    All Known Implementing Classes:

    public interface Decider
    Interface for making a choice between a set of possible options See Fates for how to use this interface.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      <K> K decide(java.lang.Object label, java.util.Set<K> options)
      User code should call this method to indicate that there is another choice to be made among the possible options.

    • Method Detail

      • decide

        <K> K decide(java.lang.Object label,
             java.util.Set<K> options)
        User code should call this method to indicate that there is another choice to be made among the possible options. The decider will pick one of the options and return it.
        Type Parameters:
        K - The type of the possible choices
        Parameters:
        label - A textual description of this decision for debugging output
        options - The possible choices
        Returns:
        The decision
